-- Japanese Sold Net 885.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-03-06T23:52:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-06/japanese-sold-net-885-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 1 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 885.4 billion yen ($9.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 441.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 21.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1348.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 657.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 269.6 billion yen in stocks, and sold 350.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 576.7
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
